com.noctarius.tengi.core.serialization.marshaller

Interface MarshallerReader<O>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - the generic value type to be un-marshalled
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DebuggableMarshaller<O>, Marshaller<O>

    public interface MarshallerReader<O>

    The MarshallerReader interface defines the un-marshalling contract for de-serializing objects from a given byte-stream. Values are read from a Decoder implementation and additional type information are available using the provided Protocol instance.

    The Decoder and Protocol implementations rely on the configured serialization framework and implemented un-marshalling should rely on implementation details of one or another serialization.

    • Method Detail

      • unmarshall

        O unmarshall(Decoder decoder,
             Protocol protocol)
      throws Exception

        This method implements the un-marshalling algorithm to read a previously marshalled internal state from the given Decoder instance. Additional protocol complexity such as required type information or child objects can be retrieved from the given Protocol instance.

        Implementations of this method must be fully thread-safe and stateless for multi-threaded usage pattern.

        Parameters:
        decoder - the Decoder to read from
        protocol - the Protocol instance for additional protocol complexity
        Returns:
        the un-marshalled value or null
        Throws:
        Exception - whenever any kind of unexpected situation happened while un-marshalling

      • unmarshall

        default O unmarshall(String fieldName,
                     Decoder decoder,
                     Protocol protocol)
              throws Exception

        This method implements the un-marshalling algorithm to read a previously marshalled internal state from the given Decoder instance. Additional protocol complexity such as required type information or child objects can be retrieved from the given Protocol instance.

        Implementations of this method must be fully thread-safe and stateless for multi-threaded usage pattern.

        This method supports field name information for the serialization debugger, whenever the debugger is enabled.

        Parameters:
        fieldName - the field name for debugging purpose
        decoder - the Decoder to read from
        protocol - the Protocol instance for additional protocol complexity
        Returns:
        the un-marshalled value or null
        Throws:
